T1  - A note on REIT bankruptcy and intraindustry information transfers: An empirical analysis
AU  - Asness, Cliff
AU  - Smirlock, Michael
JO  - Journal of Banking & Finance
VL  - 15
IS  - 6
SP  - 1171
EP  - 1182
PY  - 1991
DA  - 1991/12/01/
SN  - 0378-4266
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0378-4266(91)90056-R
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/037842669190056R
AB  - This paper examines the capital market response to the bankruptcy of Residential Resources (Res Res), a Real Estate Investment Trust (REIT). We find a significant event day value decline for a broad portfolio of REITs. REITs whose portfolios are most similar to Res Res experienced both a significant value decline and an increase in bankruptcy risk on the event day. REITs with dissimilar portfolios experienced neither of these effects. Among the REITs with similar portfolios to Res Res, leverage ratios explain 84% of the event day value declines. Our findings suggest that ignoring intraindustry firm differences can lead to spurious conclusions.
ER  - 

