T1  - A comparison of foreign exchange forward and futures prices
AU  - Polakoff, Michael A.
AU  - Grier, Paul C.
JO  - Journal of Banking & Finance
VL  - 15
IS  - 6
SP  - 1057
EP  - 1080
PY  - 1991
DA  - 1991/12/01/
SN  - 0378-4266
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0378-4266(91)90050-V
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/037842669190050V
AB  - In theory, futures resettlement should create systematic pricing differences between futures and forward contracts; however, previous empirical studies do not demonstrate such differences in the foreign exchange markets. On the other hand, inferences from these studies are suspect since they do not directly implement theortical measures of resettlement effects and are unadjusted for sub-Gaussian data properties. In this paper, these limitations are addressed through the use of the Multivariate Autoregressive Moving-Average model. Our findings provide evidence of systematic pricing influences arising from futures resettlement.
ER  - 
